column5: Opened the cottage this weekend up on NE Pigeon,  Water levels  are as high as last year but receding slowly.  Ice just gone a week.  Glad to see the Loons, Osprey and even a cormorant (no capitals) are back.  Lots of ducks, I don't know the name of, but they must be stopping on the way north.  Unfortunately got my first mosquito bite too.  Nobody on the water.
I saw a mosquito in my backyard last weekend that was the size of a quarter! Must be on her way to nwt lol
